eko: This area is called the Redirect Zone. Don't let the name fool you — nothing here goes where it claims.
eko: Phishing. Bait-and-switch. A link that promises one thing delivers something else entirely.
eko: In the real world it looks like a trusted website. A familiar logo. A form asking for your details.
eko: In here you can finally see those things for what they are — false floors, wrong doors, paths that loop back on themselves.
eko: The Frogs you've been fighting are slot machines in creature form. Their patterns are deliberate.
eko: The "near win" — you've seen it. Almost there. Just one more try. It is specifically engineered to feel like progress when there is none.
eko: The algorithm running them learned from millions of people losing. It got better at making people lose more.
eko: If something works in the real world, the system runs it in every layer. That is why it exists here too.
eko: Clear eyes. Keep moving forward.
